description:
src/lib.rs has 6+ occurrences of the closure '|e| SecretError::Backend { backend: BACKEND, source: e.into() }' (lines 156, 167, 173, 181, 185, 273, 335). Each closure has identical structure.

Suggested rewrite: introduce two private helpers
  fn backend_err(e: azure_core::Error) -> SecretError { ... }
  fn unavailable_err(e: azure_core::Error) -> SecretError { ... }
and use them as map_err arguments. Reduces 7 lines per call site to 1, removes the visual noise, and centralizes the error-conversion contract so future tweaks (e.g., adding a context message) happen once.
